f you have dual processor(i dont know if its work with other processors) i probably have solution

1.install c&c generals / c&c g zero hours
2.delete all files in "C:\Documents and Settings\xxx\My Documents\Command and Conquer Generals Data" same with zero hours
3.create file "options.ini"
4.add in file

AntiAliasing =
DrawScrollAnchor =
GameSpyIPAddress = 0.0.0.0
Gamma = 50
IPAddress = 0.0.0.0
IdealStaticGameLOD = High
LanguageFilter = false
MoveScrollAnchor =
MusicVolume = 55
Resolution = 800 600
Retaliation = yes
SFX3DVolume = 79
SFXVolume = 71
ScrollFactor = 50
SendDelay = no
StaticGameLOD = Low
UseAlternateMouse = no
UseDoubleClickAttackMove = no
VoiceVolume = 70
5. save changes
6. play a game ;]- its work in my computer intelcore2 duo
